_meanings:
{@--2@} The
full measure of anything, the whole
or entire class of things, totality;
{#jIvamAtra#} or {#prARimAtraM#} ‘the entire
class of living beings’; {#manuzyamAtro#} 
{#martyaH#} ‘every man is mortal’;  
{#vastumAtrapakzako'nupa paMhArI (hetuH)#} <ls>Tarka K.</ls>;
{#mAnuzamAtraduzkaraM karmAnuzWitaM#} <ls>Dk.</ls>

{@--3@} The
simple measure of anything, the
one thing and no more, often 
translateable by ‘mere,’ ‘only’, ‘even’;
{#jAtimAtreRa#} <ls>H. 1. 58</ls> ‘by mere caste’;
{#wiwwiBamAtreRa samudro vyAkulIkftaH#} <ls n="H.">2. 149.</ls>
‘by a mere wag-tail’, {#vAcAmAtreRa#} 
{#jApyase#} <ls>Ś. 2</ls> ‘merely by words’; so
{#arTamAtraM, saMmAnamAtraM#} <ls>Pt. 1. 83</ls>; used
with past participles {#mAtra#} may be
translated by ‘as soon as’, ‘no
sooner than’, ‘just’; {#vidDamAtraH#}  
<ls>R. 5. 51</ls> ‘as soon as pierced’, ‘when just
pierced’; {#BuktAmAtre#} ‘just after eating’;
{#pravizwamAtra eva tatramavati#} <ls>Ś. 3.</ls> &c.
